                <hr class="about-bio-divider" aria-hidden="true" />
                <p>
                  Peter Zhang is a pharmacist, technology professional, and PhD student working across healthcare, artificial intelligence, and entrepreneurship.
                </p>
                <p>
                  At ODAIA, he helps life science companies use AI to educate clinicians and improve patient outcomes. He continues to practice as a hospital pharmacist at Southlake Health and serves on the board of the Centre for Effective Practice.
                </p>
                <p>
                  His doctoral research at the University of Toronto's Leslie Dan Faculty of Pharmacy examines how and why clinicians become practicing entrepreneurs, and what that means for patients, practitioners, and health systems. He also holds a PharmD and an MBA.
                </p>
              </div>
